a) submit all DVs for cash advance for confidential activities/projects with complete required supporting documents, within seven working days from release of the check to the COA ATL concerned in a sealed envelope with a visible label “CONFIDENTIAL – For the COA ATL Only” in accordance with Section 6.3.3 (d) of the Joint Circular; 

b) ensure that all cash advances for CF shall be liquidated at year-end in compliance with Section 6.2.2.7 of the JC; 

c) submit the required documents especially those that required a ‘certified copy’ from appropriate offices to comply with the specific requirements of Sections 6.1.7 and 6.1.8.3 of the JC; 

d) ensure that the amount of CF handled by the Municipal Mayor/Special Disbursing Officer (SDO) will not exceed the maximum cash accountability covered by the fidelity bond in accordance with Treasury Circular No. 02-2019 dated April 25, 2019; and 

e) attach on each grant of the cash advance the (i) resolution of the release and utilization of the TOTAL CF duly approved by a Resolution duly approved by two-thirds (2/3) of the total membership of the Municipal Peace and Order Council (MPOC); and (ii) certified copy of the minutes of the meeting evidencing the 2/3 votes of the MPOC approving the POP and the release of the CF which are all in compliance with Sections 4.6 and 6.1.8.3 (c) of the JC.

We also recommended that Management subsequently oversee the submitted documentation for the cash liquidation of the long outstanding cash advance totaling ₱11,600,000.00. This process should be communicated and monitored until completion, to ensure the issuance of credit advice from ICFAU.

