a. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain Subsidiary Ledgers for business taxpayers; 

b. direct the Municipal Treasurer to –

i. enforce the taxpayers’ timely submission of copies of Certified ITRs on or before April 30 of each year; 

ii. assign personnel to assist in monitoring ITR submissions to ensure accurate assessment and collection of annual business taxes; 

iii. stop charging taxes to retired business owners without first identifying the variance between the tax paid during the year and the tax due based on current year gross sales or receipts before the business is officially considered retired; 

iv. assign an inspector to each application for business termination, with the responsibility of verifying the operational status by visiting the business address; and 

v. attend seminars on books examination or assign qualified personnel to conduct examinations of the books of accounts of business owners; 

c. ensure that the Revenue Code is regularly updated, adhering to the provisions of Section 191 of RA No. 7160, with updates conducted no more frequently than once every five years; and 

d. consider expediting the establishment of a BPLO assigned in assessing business taxes.

