The Commission on Audit recommended and Management agreed to instruct the:
(a) Municipal Treasurer to: (i) consider requesting to the systems developer the inclusion of summary of collectibles during the year to facilitate report generation or prepare duly certified list showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for year based on the assessment roll and furnish the Municipal Accountant at the beginning of the year; and (ii) implement procedures and strategies on how to further improve collection efficiency through publishing yearly the notice of delinquency once a week for two consecutive weeks in a newspaper of general circulation; and including remarks/statement regarding the reason/s for non-collection or non-payment in the certified list of all real property tax delinquencies which remained uncollected or unpaid for at least once a year, with a request for assistance in the enforcement of the remedies for collection submitted to the Sanggunian;
(b) Municipal Accountant consider requesting from the Commission on Audit’s Accounting Systems Development and Other Services Office (ASDOSO) under the Government Accountancy Sector the installation of enhanced New Government Accounting System (e-NGAS) which will aid them in recording transactions, financial statement preparation, among others, but also to facilitate the maintenance of Subsidiary Ledgers related to RPT/SET Receivables to provide reconciliation with records of MTO as well as to support the balance reflected in the financial statements

