On the water consumption of market -
- consider the (i) transfer the water connections of market stalls directly to MARIWAD in order to save time, fund and effort from enforcing actions against defaulting owners of sub-meters; or (ii) to create/craft clear-cut/written and approved guidelines for the detailed procedures in the over-all operations in the distribution, collection and recording of water consumption in the Mariveles Public Market and the duties and responsibilities of the assigned personnel/employees, which shall include, (without prejudice to the Management’s decision in incorporating additional controls);
- improved procedures of water meter reading and period when to conduct he reading, computation of amounts to be billed, deadline of payments and penalties of late payments of water consumption (to cover expenses on the disconnection/reconnection);
- the utilization of Microsoft Excel (IF Functions) or equivalent program which will aid in the computation of more accurate information and preparation of individual billing statement and Summary of Monthly Billings with just few clicks;
- the preparation of Summary of Monthly Billings and individual billing statement as signed by the preparer and to be submitted to the Municipal Administrator or his representative for the counterchecking of its computation;
- the manner of distribution of copies of pre-numbered individual billing statements or statement of accounts, to wit: Original – Consumer/Owner of sub-meter Duplicate – COA (as attachment to OR/AF No. 51) Triplicate – Market file;
- the method of setting up the receivables based on the computed and approved water billings of a given month and the maintenance of subsidiary ledger per lessee/owner of sub-meter by the Municipal Accountant’s Office;
- the periodic reconciliation of Municipal Market Administration Office’s records related to market collection with the subsidiary ledger maintained in the Municipal Accountant’s Office;
- the daily intact remittance of the collector to the MTO and the corresponding deposit of the latter to the agency depository bank;
- the recording of water collections by crediting water expenses (to remove the water expenses of stallholders in the records of Market);
- the salaries/wages of person/s directly involve in Mariveles Public Market and other expenses directly incurred with the water connection, disconnection and reconnection; and
- the Market Administrator’s responsibility in the strict enforcement of policies, rules and regulations for Market-Water operations;
b. instruct the Municipal Accountant to (i) maintain subsidiary records for the LEEs; and (ii) prepare Statement of Financial Condition, Statement of Financial Performance and Statement of Cash Flows for the market and other economic enterprises of the Municipality to (a) determine whether the income generated by the public utilities or economic enterprises are sufficient to meet their respective operating costs; and (b) provide adequate information as to the assets, liabilities, equity, receipts, transfers and expenditures of each special account;
c. direct the Market Committee and other market officials to (ii) revise pertinent sections of the 1997 Market Code which were found to be outdated (e.g. rental rates and composition of Market Committee); and (iii) strictly implement the stipulations of the Market Code to protect government’s welfare; and
d. instruct the Municipal Engineer and Market Administrator to immediately facilitate the request of transfer of electrical lines of stallholders from the Municipal’s mother meter directly to PENELCO to lessen expenses of the Mariveles Public Market; and
e. consider the inclusion of (i) the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant or their representatives in the Mariveles Public Market Board/Committee to perform periodic inspection and review of municipal market operations and guaranteeing that market operations are economically viable and self-reliant; and (ii) representative of Market Vendors to protect the stallholders’ interest.

